James D. WILLIAMS was born in 1843 in Kentucky. He died on 2 December 1907 at the age of 64 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He was buried in Utica Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: James Byrd WILLIAMS Jr. and unknown .

Spouse: Mary Margaret WILLIAMS. Mary Margaret WILLIAMS and James D. WILLIAMS were married on 13 October 1865 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Utica. Children were: Henry J. WILLIAMS, Jennie M. WILLIAMS, Martha Vernon "Mattie" WILLIAMS.

James Delbert WILLIAMS was born in 1910 in Mooresville Twp., Livingston, Missouri. He died in Houston, Harris, Texas. Parents: John Lawrence "Bud" WILLIAMS and Maude Mae LILLY.James E. WILLIAMS was born about 1858 in Missouri.

Spouse: Rebecca . Rebecca and James E. WILLIAMS were married. Children were: Oscar Clinton WILLIAMS.

James Ernest WILLIAMS was born in 1897. He died in 1969 at the age of 72.

Spouse: Mildred Lucille ALLEY. Mildred Lucille ALLEY and James Ernest WILLIAMS were married on 16 April 1934 in Carrollton, Carroll, Missouri. The bride was of Ludlow, the groom of Carrollton. Children were: Nancy Patricia WILLIAMS.

James Franklin WILLIAMS was born in 1851. He died in 1931 at the age of 80. He was buried in Potlatch, Latah, Idaho.

Spouse: Ada F. PROCTOR. Ada F. PROCTOR and James Franklin WILLIAMS were married.

James H. WILLIAMS was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Elizabeth TURNER. Elizabeth TURNER and James H. WILLIAMS were married on 28 March 1861 in Grundy Co., Missouri.

James H. WILLIAMS was born on 10 August 1872. He died on 26 November 1963 at the age of 91. He was buried in Cushing, Payne, Oklahoma.

Spouse: Ica Frances BOYLE. Ica Frances BOYLE and James H. WILLIAMS were married.

James Harvey "Harve" WILLIAMS was born on 20 June 1827 in Virginia. He died on 7 February 1905 at the age of 77 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 9 February 1905 in Edgewood Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. He came to Livingston County with his parents and siblings in 1844.

Parents: Capt. John Burke WILLIAMS and Mary "Polly" HALE.

Spouse: Mary Elizabeth "May" STERLING. Mary Elizabeth "May" STERLING and James Harvey "Harve" WILLIAMS were married on 30 January 1866 in Livingston Co., Missouri. Bride and groom were of Livingston Co. Children were: William Frederick WILLIAMS, Elizabeth "Lizzie" WILLIAMS, Joseph E. WILLIAMS, Ella WILLIAMS, Mattie WILLIAMS, Edward "Ed" WILLIAMS, Kate WILLIAMS.

James Howard WILLIAMS was born on 12 July 1903 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He died on 20 March 1918 at the age of 14 in Jackson Twp., Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 22 March 1918 in Gutheridge Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. A gravestone is found in Edgewood Cemetery, Chillicothe. Parents: William Frederick WILLIAMS and Katherine Wright "Kate" MOSELEY.James L. WILLIAMS was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Minnie MILLER. Minnie MILLER and James L. WILLIAMS were married. Children were: Allen Luther WILLIAMS.

James Lester WILLIAMS was born on 4 June 1921 in Utica, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 14 March 1996 at the age of 74 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 18 March 1996 in St. Columban Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Edmund Allen WILLIAMS and Lottie Ann ALNUTT.

Spouse: Minnie Kathryn MARTIN. Minnie Kathryn MARTIN and James Lester WILLIAMS were married in February 1942 in Kansas City, Wyandotte, Kansas. Children were: Don Lester WILLIAMS.

Spouse: LaVerna DOUGLAS. LaVerna DOUGLAS and James Lester WILLIAMS were married on 17 March 1973 in Carrollton, Carroll, Missouri. James and LaVerna were childless.

James Monroe WILLIAMS was born on 17 March 1870 in Sturges, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 13 December 1919 at the age of 49 in Long Beach, Los Angeles, California. He was buried in Long Beach, Los Angeles, California. Parents: George Augustin WILLIAMS Jr. and Elizabeth Herndon JONES.James Ray "Jim" WILLIAMS was born on 1 December 1944 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 11 May 1993 at the age of 48 in Grundy Co., Missouri. He was buried on 15 May 1993 in Anderson Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Earl Everett WILLIAMS and Hazel Marie REYNOLDS.

Spouse: Evelyn Marie FRIZZELL. Evelyn Marie FRIZZELL and James Ray "Jim" WILLIAMS were married on 26 June 1964 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Children were: Naioma WILLIAMS, Natlie WILLIAMS.

Jandi E. WILLIAMS was born (date unknown). Parents: Timothy E. "Sam" WILLIAMS and Janice Faye "Jan" LAWSON.

Spouse: Scott METZ. Jandi E. WILLIAMS and Scott METZ were married.

Jane Ellen WILLIAMS was born on 23 February 1931 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. She died on 7 June 2012 at the age of 81 in Trenton, Grundy, Missouri. There was cremation. A ceremony was conducted on 9 Jun 2012 with inurement postponed until a later date. She was buried in Hutchison Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Guy "Tip" WILLIAMS and Maude Louise SCOTT.

Spouse: John Edward GLADIEUX. Jane Ellen WILLIAMS and John Edward GLADIEUX were married on 4 September 1948 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Chillicothe. Guy Williams, father of Jane, gives consent. Children were: James Edward GLADIEUX, Brenda Jean GLADIEUX, Cynthia Maude GLADIEUX, Robert Franklin GLADIEUX, Jon Dale GLADIEUX.

Jane W. WILLIAMS was born on 13 January 1866 in Freedom Twp., Cattarauqus, New York. She died on 19 July 1943 at the age of 77 in State Hospital #2, St. Joseph, Missouri. The gravestone shows a death year of 1941, conflicting with the death certificate. Her usual residence was in Cowgill, Caldwell Co., Missouri. She was buried in Cowgill Cemetery, Caldwell, Missouri. Parents: David Powell WILLIAMS and Joanna "Joan" WILLIAMS.

Spouse: Griffith David OWENS. Jane W. WILLIAMS and Griffith David OWENS were married about 1889. Children were: Esther Joan OWENS.

She died on 4 October 1913 at the age of 78 in Blue Mound Twp., Livingston, Missouri. She was buried on 5 October 1913 in Welsh Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. She is also identified as Joan Powell. Parents: Thomas WILLIAMS and Anna .

Spouse: David Powell WILLIAMS. Joanna "Joan" WILLIAMS and David Powell WILLIAMS were married on 7 December 1859. Children were: Anne WILLIAMS, Margaret "Maggie" WILLIAMS, Joanna WILLIAMS, Jane W. WILLIAMS, Catherine Alice WILLIAMS, Miriam WILLIAMS, Elizabeth WILLIAMS, Edward Joshua WILLIAMS.

Joanna WILLIAMS was born in March 1864 in Wales. She died in 1931 at the age of 67 in Kansas City, Wyandotte, Kansas. Parents: David Powell WILLIAMS and Joanna "Joan" WILLIAMS.

Spouse: Charles A. MORGAN. Joanna WILLIAMS and Charles A. MORGAN were married on 17 September 1889 in Livingston Co., Missouri. Bride and groom were of Livingston Co. John Morgan, father of the groom, gives consent. Children were: Carrie A. MORGAN, John E. MORGAN, Gladys A. MORGAN.

Spouse: Elizabeth SPRINGLE. Elizabeth SPRINGLE and John WILLIAMS were married. Children were: Dr. John Springle WILLIAMS.

John WILLIAMS was born on 23 June 1822 in South Wales. He died on 21 January 1893 at the age of 70. He was buried in Welsh Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri.

Spouse: Mary THOMAS. Mary THOMAS and John WILLIAMS were married. Children were: Margaret J. WILLIAMS, William WILLIAMS, Mary Ann WILLIAMS, Eleanor Dora WILLIAMS.

John WILLIAMS was born about 1843 in Missouri. Parents: William WILLIAMS and Matilda .Capt. John Burke WILLIAMS was born on 18 November 1799 in Hoges Chapel, Giles, Virginia. He died on 20 February 1904 at the age of 59 in Dawn, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Daniel Henry WILLIAMS and Elizabeth DAVIES.

Spouse: Margaret E. Lewis . Margaret E. Lewis and John Henry WILLIAMS were married in 1865 in Wisconsin. Children were: Thomas Lewis WILLIAMS, Daniel Roderick WILLIAMS, John Roger WILLIAMS.

John Henry "Alonzo" WILLIAMS was born on 3 April 1851 in Texas. He died on 5 November 1927 at the age of 76 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He was buried on 7 November 1927 in Mooresville Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Alonzo Williams was brought to Livingston County as a slave when still a small child, accompanied by a parent or guardian. A descendant describes Alonzo as "99 44/100 percent white" but he was raised as an African-American. The 1900 census taker, Nat Fiske, termed him "black, " probably because his wife was of African-American origin.

The 1920 census identifies his birthplace as Texas, with both parents born in Tennessee.

Spouse: Anna ALLEN. Anna ALLEN and John Henry "Alonzo" WILLIAMS were married on 1 May 1884 in Mooresville, Livingston, Missouri. The groom was of Daviess Co., the bride of Livingston Co. She is identified as Anna Kinner in the marriage record. Children were: James WILLIAMS, Maud WILLIAMS, John Lawrence "Bud" WILLIAMS, Edmund Allen WILLIAMS, Charles Albert WILLIAMS, infant WILLIAMS, Lucy Mae WILLIAMS, Floyd Roosevelt WILLIAMS, Lena Pha WILLIAMS, Henry Preston WILLIAMS.

John Henry WILLIAMS was born on 5 June 1883 in Mercer Co., Missouri. He died on 18 December 1958 at the age of 75 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried in Anderson-Smith Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Green Harvey WILLIAMS and Isadora NORRIS.

Spouse: Minnie May GORDON. Minnie May GORDON and John Henry WILLIAMS were married on 8 November 1906 in Tampa, Hillsborough, Florida. Children were: Arthur Byron WILLIAMS, Hazel M. WILLIAMS, Frances Grace WILLIAMS, Ethel Merrett WILLIAMS, Vernon Leo "Bunny" WILLIAMS, Rose WILLIAMS, Dale WILLIAMS.

John Lawrence "Bud" WILLIAMS was born on 24 June 1889 in Mooresville, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 16 November 1918 at the age of 29 in Mooresville, Livingston, Missouri. His obit says he died Sunday, November 17, 1918. He was buried on 17 November 1918 in Mooresville Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. In 1918 he had a wife and six children and was unemployed. Parents: John Henry "Alonzo" WILLIAMS and Anna ALLEN.

Spouse: Maude Mae LILLY. Maude Mae LILLY and John Lawrence "Bud" WILLIAMS were married on 28 June 1908 in Mooresville, Livingston, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Mooresville. Children were: Pauline WILLIAMS, James Delbert WILLIAMS, Herbert WILLIAMS, Claude WILLIAMS, Lena Mae WILLIAMS, Leona K. WILLIAMS, Robert E. WILLIAMS.

John Maston WILLIAMS was born on 1 January 1870 in Utica, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 14 January 1950 at the age of 80. Parents: George Edward "Bud" WILLIAMS and Rebecca Frances CARSON.

Spouse: Jennie MCMILLEN. Jennie MCMILLEN and John Maston WILLIAMS were married on 31 August 1892 in Utica, Livingston, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Utica.

John Newton WILLIAMS was born on 27 April 1885 in Reger, Sullivan, Missouri. He died on 12 December 1962 at the age of 77 in Chillicothe Hospital, Livingston, Missouri. His home was five miles northeast of Avalon. He was buried on 14 December 1962 in Resthaven Memorial Gardens, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Thomas Benton WILLIAMS and Martha Elizabeth STONE.

Spouse: Maude May RINEHART. Maude May RINEHART and John Newton WILLIAMS were married in 1907. Children were: Catherine Irene "Katie" WILLIAMS, Mildred Alcinda WILLIAMS, Clarence WILLIAMS, Julia Elizabeth "Betty" WILLIAMS, Everett Eugene WILLIAMS.
